library(tidyverse)
economist <- read_csv("data/EconomistData.csv")

p1 <- ggplot(economist, aes(x = CPI, y = HDI))
p2 <- p1 + geom_point()
print(p2)



1.2

1.2.1 aesregion

p3 <- p1 + geom_point(aes(color = Region))
print(p3)



1.2.2 aes

p1 + geom_point(aes(color = "blue"))



1.2.3 aes

p1 + geom_point(color = "blue")



1.2.4 +

p3 <- p1 +
  geom_point(shape = 1,                            # shape=1
             size = 2.5, 
             aes(color = Region)) +                
  geom_smooth(method = "lm",
              color = "darkred",                                
              formula = y~ poly(x, 2),             # 
              se = FALSE)                          # SE
print(p3)



1.2.5 +

p4 <- p1 + 
  geom_point(shape = 21,                         # shape=21
             size = 3,                           # 3 
             fill = "white",                     # 
             stroke = 1.5,                       # 1.5
             aes(color = Region)) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm",
              color = "red",
              aes(linetype = "R^2 = 56%"),       # 
              formula = y~ poly(x, 2),           # 
              se = FALSE)                        # SE
print(p4)



1.2.6 

library(ggrepel)                            # ggplot2


dat <- economist %>%
  filter(Country %in% c("New Zealand","Norway","Singapore","Germany","United States",
                        "United Kingdom","Japan","Britain","Barbados","France",
                        "Spain","Botswana","CapVerde","Bhutan",
                        "Rwanda","Italy","Brazil","Greece","China",
                        "South Africa","India","Argentina","Russia",
                        "Venezuela","Iraq","Congo","Myanmar","Sudan","Afghanistan"))


p5 <- p4 +                                  # P4
  geom_text_repel(data = dat,               # 
                  force = 0.5,              # repulsion force
                  hjust = 0.1,              # 
                  size = 2,                 # 
                  aes(label = Country),     # 
                  max.overlaps = 30,        # 
                  box.padding = 0.1)        # 
print(p5)



1.2.7 XY

p6 <- p5 +
  scale_x_continuous("Corruption Perceptions Index, 2011 (10 = least corrupt)", #  x 
                     breaks = 1:10,                                             #  x 110
                     limits = c(1,10.2),                                        #  x 
                     expand = c(0,0)) +            #  x 0
  scale_y_continuous("Human Development Index, 2011 (1 = best)",                #  y 
                     breaks = seq(0.2,1,0.1),      #  y 0.210.1
                     limits = c(0.2,1.0)) +        #  y 
  scale_linetype_discrete(labels = paste0(expression(R^2)," = 56%"))   # 
                                                   # expression() 

print(p6)

1.2.10.4 

p9 <- p8 +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),                        # 
        panel.grid.major.y = element_line(color = "grey",linetype = "solid"),   # Y
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),                                   # X
        axis.line.x = element_line(color = "black"),                            # XX
        axis.text.x = element_text(color = "black",size = 12),                  # X12
        axis.ticks.length.x = unit(-0.2, "cm"),                                 # 
        axis.ticks.length.y = unit(0.5, "cm"),            
        axis.ticks.y = element_line(color = "grey"),
        axis.text.y = element_text(color = "black",size = 12),
        axis.title = element_text(face = "italic"),                             # XY
        plot.caption.position = "plot",                                         # caption
        plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0),            # captionhvh=0h=1
        legend.position = "top",                           # 
        legend.box = "horizontal",                         # 
        legend.title = element_blank(),                    # title
        legend.key = element_blank(),                      # 
        legend.justification=c(-0.15,1)) +                 # 
  guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 1,order=1))          # 


print(p9)
